# Short Reflection Report

Working on this project gave me practical experience with data analysis using NumPy and Pandas. Before starting, I understood the basic concepts of these libraries, but this task helped me apply them to a real dataset. I learned how to load and explore data, identify missing values and duplicate records, clean the dataset, and perform common data manipulation tasks such as filtering, sorting, grouping, and aggregation. Creating a new feature also helped me understand how feature engineering can improve data analysis.

One of the main challenges I faced was deciding how to handle missing values appropriately. Instead of simply removing rows, I learned that using statistical methods such as the median for numerical data and the mode for categorical data helps preserve more information. Another challenge was understanding which Pandas functions were most suitable for different operations, especially when grouping data and calculating summary statistics. I resolved these issues by carefully reading the documentation, reviewing examples, and testing different approaches until I achieved the expected results.

Overall, this project improved my confidence in working with structured datasets and strengthened my understanding of the data preprocessing workflow. I also gained experience in organizing a project professionally with proper documentation, screenshots, and a clear GitHub repository structure. These skills will be valuable in future machine learning and data science projects, where clean and well-prepared data is essential for producing reliable results.
